> Inspired by Japanese teriyaki flavours, Chef Lizzy has conjured up some culinary magic
> with this super quick pork and rice dish. The key to the stickiness of the pork is
> in bubbling the marinade down to the right consistency. Be patient people, it'll be
> worth it!

Mix together the @teriyaki marinade powder{15%g} and @teriyaki marinade paste{50%g} in
a #mixing bowl{}, then add the @diced pork{280%g}.

Mix well with your hands to coat the pork then set aside.

> TIP: Remember to wash your hands after handling raw meat!

Trim the @green beans{150%g} then chop into thirds.

Trim the ends from the @spring onion{3} then finely slice.

Heat a splash of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Add the pork and its marinade and stir-fry, ~{3%minutes}.

Add the green beans and half the spring onion and stir-fry for another ~{3%minutes}.

Lower the heat, pour the @water{75%ml} into the frying pan and simmer gently for
~{2%minutes} until the pork is cooked through and sticky.

> TIP: The pork is cooked when it is no longer pink in the middle.

Toss through half the @sesame seeds{15%g}.

Meanwhile, squeeze the pouch, tear the strip and microwave the @steamed basmati rice{1}
at 800W for ~{2%minutes} (or stir-fry for ~{3%minutes} in a dry frying pan over a
medium-high heat).

Serve the rice in bowls topped with the sticky pork.

Finish with a sprinkling of the remaining sesame seeds and spring onion. Enjoy!